<br>
Please be aware that when he is killed the gnolls (waves of 10-12 level 44ish) invade the town and kill everyone, merchants, quest givers, even the banker.<br>
<br>
If you have a force assembled to defend the town it is a fun and rewarding event. If not then you seriously endanger people currently in the town and seriously inconvenience those who visit it before - eventually - the gnolls go home and the normal occupants start to respawn.<br>
<br>
Just a plea for consideration. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suometar>Suometar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/03 1:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5304.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://koti.welho.com/kvitika2/pieni.jpg width=50 height=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please don't start a war you are not going to finish</span><hr size=1> Barducks' head is needed for a quest. I wouldn't kill him just for the heck of it, but if I need to finish the quest I would, and have. Once duo, and once with a small group. We weren't able to save all the townspeople, though we tried, but we always warned the zone before triggering the event. <br>
